events.pleaseNote: Over 18s only. ID Required. No Refunds will be given for incorrect ticket purchasing. Under 25s require ID (passport/ driving licence) to purchase alcohol. No smoking. A max of 4 tickets per person and per household applies for the presale, rising to a max of 8 tickets per person and per household for the general sale. Tickets in excess of this will be cancelled.

ticketLimit.info: Please note: A max of 4 tickets per person and per card applies during the presale. This will increase to a max of 8 tickets per person and per card during general on sale.

venues.name: O2 Victoria Warehouse Manchester

boxOfficeInfo.phoneNumberDetail: Ticketmaster is our official booking partner, selling tickets for all Academy Music Group venues in the UK. You can book online. Our terms and conditions of entry are here.
boxOfficeInfo.openHoursDetail: Opening hours vary. Check our venue's box office details on our Contact page. We'll have opening times, stage times (if we know them on show days) and curfew times if they're out of the ordinary for seasoned gig-goers (7pm-11pm) on the event page of the venue website and social channels, too. All timings are subject to change, so check before you travel.
boxOfficeInfo.acceptedPaymentDetail: Card only. This venue is cashless.
boxOfficeInfo.willCallDetail: Please bring a copy of the booking confirmation, ID and the debit or credit card you used to buy them.

venues.parkingDetail: We're easy to get to by all major approach roads, including the M61 and M60 motorways and M602 at Junction 3. If using the M50633, exit to Salford/Trafford Park. From the M56 and M60, exit at Junctions 7 or 8. Our postcode for sat nav is M17 1AB. We do not have any parking available, but please click here to find more information on local parking options nearby. Just so you, parking options adjacent to our venue are not affiliated to O2 Victoria Warehouse and not official event car parks. Please check times and prices as they may vary.
venues.accessibleSeatingDetail: Give us a call or drop us an email for more details on wheelchair-accessible spaces at shows.

generalInfo.generalRule: No cameras, video cameras or audio recording. No food, bottles, cans or alcohol to be brought onto the premises. No smoking. Security measures are in place so there will be bag checks on arrival. Only one small bag per person is permitted, and it must not be bigger than A4 size. Height: 29.7cm Width: 21cm Depth: 15cm Large bags, including rucksacks, are not allowed and there are no facilities to leave any luggage so please make alternative arrangements. If you really have to bring a bag and its preferable you don't, please make sure its small.
generalInfo.childRule: It's always best to check the age restrictions for each event in advance as they vary from show to show. Most shows are 14+ (and that means you can come without an adult over 18 and be in the stalls area) but please remember to check when you book as it can vary from show to show. Always look for admission age policies and signs such as 14+, 16+, 18+, 21+ before you book and remember to carry proof of age if you need it. Find out more about age restrictions and what we accept as ID in our FAQs.

Booking Tickets

venues.name: Historic Crew Stadium

boxOfficeInfo.phoneNumberDetail: Historic Crew Stadium Information General Crew SC and Stadium Information: (614) 447-2739 Ticket Office: (614) 447-4169 Crew SC Group Tickets: (614) 447-4159 Stadium Event Group Tickets: (614) 447-4169
boxOfficeInfo.openHoursDetail: Stadium Hours - Ticket Office and Crew SC Gear Store Monday-Friday: 9:00am - 5:00pm Saturday - Sunday: Closed except on event days. Ticket office opens at 10:00am on weekend event days.
boxOfficeInfo.acceptedPaymentDetail: Visa, Mastercard, American Express, Discover and Cash
boxOfficeInfo.willCallDetail: Will Call is located at the Southwest corner of the Stadium next to Gate 5. Guests may pick-up will call during Ticket Office hours. Guest must present actual credit card, picture I.D. and confirmation number to retrieve their tickets.

venues.parkingDetail: General Parking is $15.00 for Crew SC matches. Parking prices vary for all other Stadium Events. Please call the Historic Crew Stadium Ticket Office at (614) 447-4169 for event information.
venues.accessibleSeatingDetail: Special Seating is available for guests with disabilities. Please contact the Historic Crew Stadium Ticket Office at (614) 447-4169.

generalInfo.generalRule: Outside food and beverage is prohibited in Historic Crew Stadium. Use of video cameras or recording devices of any kind are prohibited. Cameras with detachable lenses are prohibited for sporting events. For Historic Crew Stadium special events, cameras are generally not permitted; however camera usage is dictated on a show by show basis. Call the Historic Crew Stadium Ticket Office at (614) 447-4169 for more information.
generalInfo.childRule: Columbus Crew SC Matches: Children two (2) years and younger are not required to have a ticket for admission, but must sit on the lap of a ticketed guardian. Historic Crew Stadium Events: Policies vary per event. Call the Historic Crew Stadium Ticket Office at (614) 447-4169 for event information.
